## Implemented
- Added `renderer-typst` as the primary renderer feature and kept `typst` as a compatibility alias.
- Added `renderer-minimal` as the explicit minimal-backend feature and included it in the default feature set so the feature matrix matches the approved contract without changing runtime behavior.
- Moved render configuration types (`BuiltInTheme`, `LayoutMode`, `PageSize`, `ThemeConfig`) into `core` so `core` no longer depends on `api` types.
- Split renderer adapters into `render/mod.rs`, `render/minimal.rs`, `render/plan.rs`, and `render/typst.rs` to better match the intended adapter structure.
- Extended the shared render plan to carry structured image elements instead of text-only lines.
- Updated the Typst adapter to inject memory-backed image assets through `typst-as-lib` static file resolution, so memory-only resolver flows now work with the Typst backend.
- Expanded the error model with `InvalidConfiguration`, `TypstCompile`, `TypstExport`, and `TypstAsset` variants.
- Added feature-matrix coverage in `tests/feature_matrix.rs` and a runnable harness in `scripts/validate-feature-matrix.sh`.
- Extended the feature-matrix coverage and validation harness to exercise `--features renderer-minimal` explicitly.
- Updated README and crate docs to reflect the new renderer feature contract and memory-backed Typst behavior.

